The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, June 21, 2004 				 Shinde nod to Pak mission
																								Mumbai, June 20 (PTI): Pakistan will be allowed to set up a consulate in Mumbai on a reciprocal basis, with India establishing a similar set-up in Karachi, chief minister Sushil Kumar Shinde has said.																								Relations between the two countries are improving and the process is on to locate sites for the consulates in the respective countries, the Maharashtra chief minister said at the annual day function of the press club last night. He hoped that setting up consulates would help strengthen ties between the neighbouring nations.																								Shinde also announced a development package for Mumbai Press Club involving a grant of Rs 25 lakh from the Chief Ministers Relief Fund, allotment of land in Navi Mumbai and steps to implement the housing scheme for needy journalists.
